<seg id=1> Minister Sa considers that it is very likely that Hua An is guilty of his accused crimes including pederasty. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (AFP-Sydney)The Malaysian Chief Minister of Salaoyue State, Taiyi Mmamu said that, the former Vice Prime Minister, Hua An, who was arrested, is very likely to be found guilty for all the charges he was accused of, including pederasty. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> While talking during an interview by Australian newspaper yesterday, he said that, he knows Hua An "quite well", and he believes that it is very likely that Hua An will be found guilty for all the charges. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> He said that: " I have already known the charges he is facing. </seg>
<seg id=5> I think that it is very likely that he will be found guilty, </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> After being removed from his position in early September, and launching a series of processions for reformation, Hua An was arrested on September 20 under the security prescript, facing 10 charges which include 5 charges of pederasty and 5 charges of corruption. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> He appeared in public for the first on Tuesday, 9 days after his arrest. He appeared to have black and blue bruises on his left eye and hands. He denied all charges against him. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Taiyi is currently attending an International Alumni Association's meeting at Adelaide. </seg>
<seg id=9> He expressed that he had not contacted Hua An lately. However, he does not worry about his situation, and he does not worry that Hua An will not have a fair trail, either. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> He said that: " The law is fair and square...... if he is innocent, I believe he will be set free. </seg>
<seg id=11> However, if he is found guilty, he should be punished in the same way as any other Malaysian citizens. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Taiyi also blamed Hua An for damaging the International image of Malaysia. </seg>
<seg id=13> He said that: " I think, what really damaged our image were Hua An's speeches, but not what happened here." </seg>
</p>
